The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 HFCL has launched a per-second pulse service. Under this scheme, which has been launched under the brand name Ping, each call costs a paise per second. It will cater to customers in Punjab and Chandigarh. HFCL has invested Rs 100 crore in launching the service and will invest another Rs 20 crore to extend it, the company said in a statement.

 Ford India will export the Fiesta to South Africa. It will be the first completely built vehicle export programme from the companys Chennai plant. Ford India plans to initially export around 5,000 vehicles a year. The Fiesta was first showcased in South Africa during the 2006 Auto Africa exhibition.

 CARE has assigned the AAA rating to the umbrella borrowing programme of the National Bank for Agriculture and Rural Development (Nabard). The rating reflects Nabards good performance as a refinancing, supervisory and development institution for the agriculture and rural sectors.

 Bajaj Auto has launched the XCD 125 motorbike with digital twin spark-swirl induction engine. The bike will offer 150cc features, 125cc performance and 100cc mileage.

